Signature Events
Annual Installation Banquet
The Ormond Beach Chamber of Commerce Annual Banquet and Installation of Officers brings together business leaders and City dignitaries to recognize contributions made by Members, highlight Chambers achievements throughout the year and welcome new Board of Directors.Â  This prestigious event includes reception and dinner.
This event will be held in January 2026.

This is the longest running Fundraising event of the Chamber and takes place on the last Friday in April. Did you know more business deals are closed on the golf course than anywhere else?Â Â We Just celebrated 55 years of the tournament. This event is the perfect opportunity to meet new customers and have a fun day on the golf Course at the same time.

Women2Women Luncheon
This event takes place twice a year in the Spring and Fall . The Luncheon isÂ  designed to bring professional business women together to meet and network with each other. The luncheon features an inspiring keynote speaker to learn about their success and challenges in the business world.
Watch the calendar for open registration.Â

State of the City Luncheon
The Chamber in partnership with the City of Ormond Beach hosts it's Annual State of the City Luncheon on the 2nd Tuesday in October. The luncheon features a program presented by the City Commission on the futureÂ of Ormond Beach.
This event will be held October 2025
Reocurring Events
Business After Hours
Held monthly on the second (2nd) Wednesday of each month from 4:30 to 6:30 PM. The event is hosted by a local Chamber business member with about 50-75 in attendance.
This social relaxed event is meant for members to mix and mingle with each other and meet new and future members over drinks and appetizers.
BOSS Program
Ormond Beach Chamber of Commerce BOSS Program (Business Owners Sharing Solutions)
BOSS is an educational platform for the business community and promotes professional development. Topics will change for each event.
Economic Prosperity Hour
Held 6 times a year, every other month.Â  This event is designed as an informational meeting with Economic Prosperity updates from County and City elected officials, City staff, Ormond Mainstreet and a local residential and commercial real estate update. The event features a speaker related to Economic Development or Government Affairs. Average attendance is 50 community leaders. Members Advance online registration $10, at the door $15 and future members $25.
Morning Member Meetup
A dynamic networking event designed to kickstart your business day. Held from 8:00am - 9:00am, this early-morning gathering offers a unique opportunity to engage with fellow members before the workday begins.
Hosted at different member businesses quartly, this event provides a relaxed and informal setting for professionals to exchange ideas, build relationships, and explore new business opportunitiesâall while enjoying coffee, light refreshments, and a welcoming atmosphere.
Rise and shineâjoin us at the next Morning Member Meetup to make connections that matter!
Chamber.Coffee.Connect
We welcome new members and new representatives of chamber members to the Morning orientation as we present an overview of Chamber benefits, committees and services. The event is held quarterly in the Chamber boardroom and EXCLUSIVE to chambers members only.
Ribbon Cuttings
Ribbon cuttings are a member only benefit to qualifying businesses to celebrate the grand opening of a new location, remodel, expansion or a brand new business. Held on Thursday afternoons at 4:00 PM with the cutting at 4:30 PM.
For more information on Ribbon cutting criteria contact jgion@ormondchamber.com

Rob Ridder Scholarship Background:
The Ormond Beach Chamber of Commerce Rob Ridder Scholarship was established in 2014, and is intended to recognize students of Chamber members for outstanding educational and community service achievement. The program started by giving away 2 - $1,000 Scholarships and has grown to 8 - $1,000 Scholarships in 2023. To donate contact
Debbie Cotton
, President & CEO.
Leadership Ormond Beach
Developing Community Leaders Since 2003
The Ormond Beach Leadership Program, developed by the Ormond Beach Chamber of Commerce, is designed to engage civic-minded individuals with the issues, opportunities, and challenges facing the Ormond Beach community. Since its inception in 2003, the program has provided participants with meaningful leadership development and direct access to community leaders, city officials, and dignitaries.
This comprehensive program consists of eight (8) half-day sessions and concludes with a graduation ceremony. Each session offers a deep dive into key areas shaping the future of Ormond Beach.
Program Sessions Include:
Orientation â Day 1
Orientation â Day 2: Leadership Session & Alumni Reception
City Government Session
Health & Wellness Session
Historical Tour
Economic Development Session
Non-Profit Session
Ormond Beach Youth Leadership Program
The Ormond Beach Chamber has developed a Youth Leadership program that we think will blend both workforce and leadership.
Participants in Youth Leadership Ormond Beach will gain knowledge of the community while building relationships with like-minded peers. Through interactions with local business leaders and government officials they gained valuable insights.Â  In turn, provided these students with a solid appreciation and understanding for their community.Â  The intent of the program is to help graduates build strong connections that keep the Ormond Beach community in their hearts and minds, whatever path they ultimately choose after their high school graduation.
Sessions mirror our Leadership Ormond Beach program, however, are amended to topics that will engage our youth and highlight local internships and career opportunities at each session.Â Â  Each student earns community service hours they can apply to their Bright Future Scholarships. Program takes place in the Fall on Early Release days.Â  Contact Patty Tropea,
ptropea@ormondchamber.com
Teacher of the Quarter
This is one of our longest running programs in Chamber and has been part of our mission for over 20 years. This is an important part of our mission to promote community interest in local schools and develop leaders, the Chamber recognizes the teachers in the Ormond Beach area schools each quarter.

Certificate of Origin
The Ormond Beach Chamber of Commerce is authorized to certify Certificates of Origin for export.
A Certificate of Origin (CO) is an important international trade document attesting that goods in a particular export shipment are wholly obtained, produced, manufactured or processed in a particular country.
COs also constitute a declaration by the exporter. Virtually every country in the world considers the origin of imported goods when determining what duty will be assessed on the goods or, in some cases, whether the goods may be legally imported at all.
To determine if a CO is required, contact the Trade Information Centre of the export destination.

Membership Committees
Ambassador Committee -Â
The Ambassador role is to connect with new Chamber members to help navigate the opportunities within the Chamber and to help advise on the best ways to get engaged and meet their goals for joining. Ambassadors are the face of the Chamber for many new members and are responsible for a large portion of the touch points between the Chamber and the member. As such, it is crucial that Ambassadors have experience navigating the Chamberâs workings and are actively engaged in their own Chamber membership. It is also important that they understand the responsibility of representing the Chamber properly, have a realistic understanding of the time needed to do so, and are recognized and rewarded for their efforts.Â Â For more information on becoming an ambassador contact:Â
info@ormondchamber.com
